curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/1492' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM6010", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM6010 is a synchronous, buck DC/DC converter  with a range of 3V to 5.5V input voltage. This device is  capable to provide a 3A continuous output current. It  operates with a programmable frequency range of  300kHz to 2MHz. The SGM6010 is highly efficient with  peak efficiency at 95% when in operation. The 100%  duty cycle could make the lowest dropout.  The forced continuous pulse width modulation (PWM)  mode operation could decrease the ripple voltage to  the lowest level and reduce noise and RF interference  as well. No external power MOSFETs and Schottky  diode are required because of the internal synchronous  low on-resistance power switches. The external  compensation can improve the transient response  across the loads and output capacitors.   The SGM6010 is available in a Green TDFN-3×3-10L  package. It is rated over the -40℃ to +85℃ temperature  range.      "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/1493' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM6010", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● 3V to 5.5V Input Voltage Range  ● Up to 95% High Efficiency  ● 120mΩ Low RDS(ON) Internal Switches  ● 300kHz to 2MHz Programmable Frequency  ● 3A Output Current  ● 0.8V Reference Allows Low Output Voltages  ● Shutdown Current: 2μA (MAX)  ● 100% Duty Cycle for Lowest Dropout  ● Forced Continuous PWM Mode Operation  ● No External Power MOSFETs and Schottky Diode  Required  ● Excellent Line and Load Transient Responses  ● -40℃ to +85℃ Operating Temperature Range  ● Available in a Green TDFN-3×3-10L Package      "}'
